args: Damn! How is it so strong?!
Gah... He's overpowering me...\nAt this rate—
Guh... I... I think I'm done for...\nSorry...everyone...
I'm running out of time.\nI need to do something.
...What? I'm going to be killed by a fiend?
I apologize for startling you, but this is no\nordinary dream.
I had a similar one regarding my brother's\ndeath. It is proof that a terrible destiny\nis drawing near!
Well, if you say so. I've got no reason to\ndoubt you.
In that case, are you going to stop\nfighting fiends?
I appreciate your warning, but I can't do\nthat. Sorry.
As long as fiends continue causing trouble\nand misery, I'll be there fighting them.
...No, I have to respect your will.
But in return, I will protect you.\nI will triumph over destiny!
Stay alert! There is no telling where fiends\nmay be lurking!
(That's the fiend from my dream...\nI'm sure of it!)
There you are! Right, leave this to me—
No! I will take care of this!
Come, fiend! I shall be your opponent!
Guh... This fiend is so strong...
Hey! I'm here! Come and get me!
Gah... He's overpowering me...\nAt this rate—
(This is just how things played out\nin my dream!)
(No... I can't believe my actions ended up\ndirectly causing it to become reality!)
(Is there really nothing I can do?\nAm I completely powerless in the\nface of destiny after all?!)
Whew... I'm glad we made it in time.
Ranzal! Elly! I owe you two big-time.
Eh, coverin' for yer recklessness is kinda\nwhat we do.
Because of you, I was able to overcome\nmy nightmare and defeat fate.
Eh, we didn't do all that.
It was only because of your warning that\nwe were as cautious as we were.
If not for that, we would never have made\nit in time to save him.
So WE actually owe everythin' to YOU.
Thank you, Verica. I owe you my life.
No, this is wrong. He was only saved\nbecause the two of you interfered.
It took all of our combined efforts to\ntriumph over destiny.
You couldn't have done it alone—\nbut neither could we.
Oh, I'm such a fool! How was I not able to\nrealize that on my own?
I knew better than anyone just how\ndifficult it is to change fate, and yet\nI still tried to do it alone.
I should have tried to enlist everyone's\nhelp from the start.
There's no reason you need stand up to\ndestiny alone.
So long as we're together, we can get\nthrough anything.
I won't forget that again... Thank you so\nmuch, {player_name}.
Oh dear. He doesn't sound happy.
Yeah, I just can't seem to get him to bond\nwith me like he has with you.
Heh. I'm sure he loves you, too.
After all, he's my child—and I love you\ndearly.
Maybe he just wants to snuggle with you.\nWe have that in common.
It looks as if you're right. You're just like\none another.
Feel free to snuggle with me, too, dear.
...A dream? But who was that man I was\ntalking to?
Was that just a reflection of my desires?\nOr is this also fate...?
